lass="containbox" style="margin:auto; position:relative; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom:20px; width:98%; background-color:var(--background-color);"><div style="float:left;"><a href="/about" class="p-author"><img class="ppic" src="https://shellsharks-images.s3.amazonaws.com/surfshark.png" width="60" alt="author-image" ></a></div><div style="float:left;"><span id="author" style="font-weight:bold;">Mike Sass</span><br><span id="handle" style="color:var(--light-font-color);">@shellsharks</span></div><div style="float:right;padding:10px 0px 0px 0px;"><i class="ph ph-calendar-dot"></i> <span id="date" style="font-size:0.75em;" class="dt-published">1/16/25 09:15</span></div><br><br><br><header id="header" class="post-header"></header><div class="post-content e-content"><p>Since starting this <a href="/notes/2025/01/10/gotosocial-on-knt-host">GoToSocial</a> instance, I‚Äôve made several long-winded posts (and replies). Some examples‚Ä¶<ul><li><a href="https://malici.ous.computer/@shellsharks/statuses/01JHNXYFK1M9MZNBT07QEJF1ZH">Intro post</a><li><a href="/notes/2025/01/15/bluesky-wont-free-your-feed">Free Our Feeds rebuttal</a><li><a href="/notes/2025/01/14/curious-timing">A take on social web-related foundations</a><li>and <em>many many more</em>‚Ä¶</ul><p>Each of these I‚Äôm referring to exceed Mastodon‚Äôs 500 character post/reply limit. If it wasn‚Äôt for me having this instance, which gives me ample room to say what I want to say in a single post, you would have had seen these posts broken up into a threaded series. One of these posts was some 6000+ characters long, which would have necessitated ~13 individual posts to get my point across. Spam much? This is what I don‚Äôt understand about folks here who say they don‚Äôt want increased post limits, or from the Masto devs who seemingly refuse to budge on this issue. If I can jam everything into a single post, you can decide to read, or just scroll on past, never clicking on the ‚ÄòRead More‚Äô link to expand the post. done! But with the 500 char count, you are forced to A. scroll past all my blathering, or B. try to navigate the confusing-AF threading UI that most masto clients seem to have. <em>How. is. this. better?!</em><p>For others, you might say, ‚Äú<em>jeez, if you have so much to say, why not just make it a blog post</em>‚Äù. You‚Äôre not wrong. That‚Äôs probably a good idea‚Ä¶ but! There‚Äôs something you get by just organically, and informally typing something into this box that it hard to replicate when you are writing up a formal blog post/note. At least for me where I have to A. be at my computer, B. fill out the proper SSG front matter, C. worry about headings, markdown, etc‚Ä¶ And sometimes, it‚Äôs not a blog post. It‚Äôs just an off-the-cuff, albeit somewhat long, response to something<p>Also, I can‚Äôt count the amount of posts/replies I want to publish that are like 600 characters. So this means I have to either somehow truncate what I want to say, or god forbid, have a threaded post where the child post is like 50 characters long ü§¶‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è. There are a lot of cringey things on social media, but one thing I really despise is when people have to use the dumb üßµ or ü™° emoji before they launch into something. Like.. just have it all in one post! Oh wait, they can‚Äôt.<p>Finally, I‚Äôm someone who bookmarks, saves and references a lot of stuff I see on the web, and that includes social media posts, especially on the Fediverse where people tend to share a lot of great stuff! Having an excellent analysis of something forcibly chunked into 500 characters is pretty obnoxious when you want to bookmark something to check out later.<p>So yeah, I‚Äôm going to continue to write lonnnnnng posts, and you‚Äôll all thank me for not having to scroll past 10+ atomic posts in your feed just because you were kind enough to follow me here. Hell, this post is nearly 3k words at this point.</div><div style="bottom:-5px; text-align:right;font-size:0.75em;"><i class="ph ph-pencil"></i> 508</div><hr style="opacity:35%;margin-top: 10px;margin-bottom: 10px;width:75%;"><div id="info" class="wrapper"><div class="box 1" style="background-color:var(--background-color);"><div><i class="ph ph-map-pin-area" title="Posted from"></i> <span id="posted-from" style="font-size:0.75em;">Mac Pro 2019</span></div><div><i class="ph ph-broadcast"></i><span style="font-size:0.75em;"> Syndication:</span></div><div style="font-size:1.5em;"><span id="syndicate-to"> <span style="padding:0px 3px 0px 3px;"><a href="https://malici.ous.computer/@shellsharks/statuses/01JHQTXV2QNGR6CWW07MS1EGD3"><i class="ph ph-fediverse-logo" title="GoToSocial"></i></a></span> </span></div></div><div class="box2" style="bottom:0;"><div style="text-align:right; padding:5px 5px 5px 5px;"><a class="u-url" href=""><i class="ph ph-link" title="Permalink"></i></a> <a href="/notebook"><i class="ph ph-book-open" title="Notebook"></i></a> <a href="/"><i class="ph ph-house" title="Home"></i></a></div><div style="font-size:0.75em;color:var(--light-font-color);padding:5px 5px 0px 5px;text-align:right;"><i class="ph ph-tag"></i> <span id="tags" style="padding:0px 3px 0px 3px;"><a href="/tags?tag=technology">#technology</a></span> <span id="tags" style="padding:0px 3px 0px 3px;"><a href="/tags?tag=social">#social</a></span> <span id="tags" style="padding:0px 3px 0px 3px;"><a href="/tags?tag=fediverse">#fediverse</a></span></div></div></div></div></article><div style="margin-bottom:20px; margin-right:5px; margin-left:5px;"> <a class="prev" style="margin-right: 2em; margin-left:8px;" href="/notes/2025/01/16/challenges-and-opportunities-of-the-singular-fedi-identity#title">&laquo; Challenges and opportunities of the singular Fedi identity</a><div style="float:right;"><a class="next" href="/notes/2025/01/16/the-magic-of-pesos#title" style="margin-right: 8px;">The magic of PESOS &raquo;</a></div></div><style> .wrapper { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } img {max-width:100%}</style></div></ma